mestable.study_name: Will I Yield To God's Destiny?
mestable.study_description: Throughout the Bible, God?s people went through lots of things in periods of 40. During the 40 (days/weeks/months/years), there were trials. There was waiting. There was wandering. There was uncertainty. But then came 41! When 40 becomes 41, there is hope. There is freedom. There is power. There is destiny. Whatever your 40 may be, GET READY for 41!

mestable.study_name: The World, The Flesh and The Devil
mestable.study_description: There is a Resistance that hates the thought of you doing something great to change the world. Not some mystical force or feeling but very real power that is deadly and diabolical. It can derail your life from accomplishing something significant for God. But there is hope. The Resistance can be overpowered. The Resistance can be defeated. It's time to equip yourself for battle.

Each year we celebrate the anniversary of our American independence. Families gather around a picnic table for a meal, enjoy a fireworks display or watch the local parade. These time-honored traditions remind us of our freedom as Americans and as individuals. But true freedom has come because we are one nation under God. The freedom granted in Christ is the source of our true freedom. “So if the Son sets you free, you will be free indeed.” John 8:36 Although our nation has faced trials and challenges, we have endured.
